Olathe.Franklin R. Lanter House:
The Franklin R. Lanter House is a historic house located at 562 West Park Street in Olathe, Kansas.


== Description and history ==
The two-story, wood-framed house was built in 1901 for Franklin R. Lanter, a lumber and coal merchant. It was designed by architect George P. Washburn in the Queen Anne style, especially Free Classicism.
